stimulus:
The Illusion Game

In this reaction-time game, you will need to be as fast as possible and make correct responses by resisting different visual illusions.

Sometimes, it's very hard and you want to rely on your intuition and gut feeling to answer fast without making errors.

Don't worry, we will show you examples of each illusion before each block. Each illusion block will be repeated two times (so that you have an opportunity to improve your score!), but the order of the blocks is random.

Remember, your goal is to be as fast and accurate as possible. Good luck!

Part 1

In this part, two horizontal red lines will appear one above the other.

Your task is to select which line has a longer length as fast as you can, without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the surrounding black lines!

Press the UP or the DOWN arrow to indicate where is the longest red line.

In this example, the correct answer is the UP arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Your score for this illusion is

3043

Can you do better in the next illusion?

Part 2

In this part, two horizontal red lines will appear one above the other.

Your task is to tell the direction towards which the red lines are converging, as fast as you can, and without making errors.

Don't get distracted by the black lines!

Press the LEFT or the RIGHT arrow to indicate the direction where the red lines are pointing.

In this example, the correct answer is the LEFT arrow.

Are you ready? Press ENTER to start

Your score for this illusion is

3456

Can you do better in the next illusion?
